17
00:01:34,730 --> 00:01:35,980
=The Lead=

18
00:01:36,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 16=

19
00:01:51,320 --> 00:01:53,440
The troupe's old scripts are all here.

20
00:01:54,320 --> 00:01:56,440
Shi Wu Guan. San Di Xue.

21
00:01:56,920 --> 00:01:59,840
This one's Zhou Ren Hui Fu.

22
00:02:02,120 --> 00:02:03,360
Xia He Dong.

23
00:02:03,360 --> 00:02:05,080
Now some are all moldy.

24
00:02:05,680 --> 00:02:07,280
Others have been chewed by mice.

25
00:02:07,880 --> 00:02:10,120
We can't find one complete script.

26
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:13,800
So what if you do find one?

27
00:02:14,920 --> 00:02:16,720
The old opera takes real skill.

28
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:19,000
The effort used in modern plays

29
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:20,160
isn't the same kind at all.

30
00:02:21,720 --> 00:02:23,120
Among the actors,

31
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:24,720
me, the director,

32
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:26,480
and you,

33
00:02:26,960 --> 00:02:28,200
is anyone an expert?

34
00:02:28,880 --> 00:02:29,440
No.

35
00:02:30,600 --> 00:02:32,800
If the old opera can be liberated,

36
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:35,880
shouldn't the veteran artists
be liberated too?

37
00:02:37,250 --> 00:02:39,100
- Exactly.
- There's something wrong with that.

38
00:02:40,320 --> 00:02:41,640
What do you mean, "liberated"?

39
00:02:42,480 --> 00:02:44,440
The whole country was liberated in 1949.

40
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:46,120
So,

41
00:02:46,360 --> 00:02:47,520
are you trying to say

42
00:02:47,520 --> 00:02:49,720
those veteran artists still
live in the old society?

43
00:02:49,960 --> 00:02:51,000
Director Huang...

44
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:52,240
Call me Troupe Leader.

45
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:55,440
The Revolutionary Committee era is over.

46
00:02:55,880 --> 00:02:58,600
The title "Director Huang"
should be retired.

47
00:02:58,640 --> 00:03:00,800
Do you know what I'm thinking?

48
00:03:01,040 --> 00:03:02,720
This is no time for nitpicking.

49
00:03:03,520 --> 00:03:04,880
Nitpicking?

50
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:06,600
Deputy Troupe Leader Zhu,

51
00:03:08,120 --> 00:03:10,520
this is called political consciousness.

52
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:14,600
We must never lose
our political consciousness.

53
00:03:18,440 --> 00:03:20,000
Stop looking down.

54
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:21,840
You're the director.

55
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:24,080
If you can't direct the old opera,

56
00:03:24,080 --> 00:03:25,080
what good are you anyway?

57
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:27,320
Go and invite those three veteran artists

58
00:03:27,640 --> 00:03:28,520
back.

59
00:03:29,320 --> 00:03:31,680
Troupe Leader, let's talk about them then.

60
00:03:33,520 --> 00:03:34,840
One guards the gate.

61
00:03:34,840 --> 00:03:36,040
One manages the meals.

62
00:03:36,440 --> 00:03:37,480
One watches the theater.

63
00:03:38,040 --> 00:03:40,000
And what about the other?

64
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:41,800
Wandering around the world.

65
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:44,360
We don't even know if he's dead or alive.

66
00:03:45,200 --> 00:03:46,880
Those three old guys have been

67
00:03:48,600 --> 00:03:50,280
off the stage for over 20 years.

68
00:03:51,200 --> 00:03:52,400
Look how old they are now.

69
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:54,040
At most,

70
00:03:54,080 --> 00:03:55,600
they can do an opera excerpt.

71
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:57,480
A full-length opera is impossible.

72
00:03:58,200 --> 00:04:00,560
Isn't an opera excerpt still an opera?

73
00:04:01,600 --> 00:04:03,240
Better than having nothing to perform.

74
00:04:03,240 --> 00:04:04,080
Right?

75
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:05,600
Besides,

76
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:09,360
I heard the Provincial
Troupe's opera excerpts

77
00:04:09,360 --> 00:04:11,240
are extremely popular.

78
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:13,400
The tickets are impossible to get.

79
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:15,080
They're the Provincial Troupe.

80
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:16,200
And what are we?

81
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:19,240
Just a tiny County Troupe.

82
00:04:20,280 --> 00:04:22,320
Provincial-army vs County-regiment level.

83
00:04:22,320 --> 00:04:23,680
That's many ranks apart.

84
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:24,800
I don't need to spell it out.

85
00:04:25,520 --> 00:04:27,160
A mere bit-part player from there

86
00:04:27,160 --> 00:04:28,560
could play the lead here.

87
00:04:29,640 --> 00:04:32,160
We have only two lead performers.

88
00:04:32,520 --> 00:04:34,520
Hua Caixiang left to have a baby.

89
00:04:34,960 --> 00:04:37,560
Mi Lan's busy getting married, right?

90
00:04:42,080 --> 00:04:43,240
And let's talk about

91
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:44,880
the greenhorns in the trainee class.

92
00:04:45,480 --> 00:04:48,240
Sure, they've trained for years.

93
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:51,320
But they can't carry the show.

94
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:55,320
What matters in the old opera?

95
00:04:55,320 --> 00:04:57,240
It's the performer's real skill.

96
00:04:57,960 --> 00:04:58,800
Troupe Leader,

97
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:00,080
I won't say anything so discouraging.

98
00:05:01,440 --> 00:05:03,040
We'll do exactly as you asked.

99
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:05,720
We'll just wing it and force the show.

100
00:05:05,960 --> 00:05:07,520
But I have one question for you.

101
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:11,280
Where will we get the opera costumes?

102
00:05:12,040 --> 00:05:13,200
That's a serious problem.

103
00:05:15,160 --> 00:05:16,000
Exactly.

104
00:05:16,720 --> 00:05:18,160
Those costumes

105
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:20,480
were all burned to ashes.

106
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:25,880
Exactly.

107
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:33,080
Now, no one watches the new plays,

108
00:05:33,520 --> 00:05:35,480
and we can't do the old opera.

109
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:38,160
It's been over a year since we had

110
00:05:38,160 --> 00:05:39,360
any shows to perform.

111
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:41,040
In my opinion,

112
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:43,840
we should just fold and disband.

113
00:05:44,920 --> 00:05:45,800
I agree.

114
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:49,240
Deputy Troupe Leader Zhu,

115
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:51,200
you draft a proposal

116
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:53,800
to disband the County Troupe,

117
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:55,800
and I'll submit it for you.

118
00:05:56,200 --> 00:05:57,040
What do you think?

119
00:05:59,200 --> 00:06:00,960
Now you're making me look bad.

120
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:05,080
Let me be clear with you.

121
00:06:06,160 --> 00:06:09,320
The county leaders are quite unhappy with

122
00:06:09,320 --> 00:06:11,240
our troupe's recent performance.

123
00:06:11,800 --> 00:06:14,760
As Deputy Troupe Leader
in charge of operations,

124
00:06:15,320 --> 00:06:16,400
if the troupe has no shows,

125
00:06:16,400 --> 00:06:18,040
you will be held responsible.

126
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:20,040
That's not very fair to say.

127
00:06:20,040 --> 00:06:22,960
I told you to provide against a rainy day.

128
00:06:22,960 --> 00:06:23,840
And what did you say?

129
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:28,480
What did I say?

130
00:06:30,240 --> 00:06:31,120
You said,

131
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:34,320
"How do we know which way the rain falls?"

132
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:36,080
Was I wrong?

133
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:41,000
Was I wrong to say that?

134
00:06:42,920 --> 00:06:45,240
Enough, we'll do Bi Shang Liang Shan.

135
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:47,960
Get me a plan immediately.

136
00:06:48,480 --> 00:06:50,000
I need to report to the county.

137
00:06:50,520 --> 00:06:51,720
Take this seriously.

138
00:07:36,520 --> 00:07:37,560
Keep your leg up.

139
00:07:37,760 --> 00:07:38,720
Just keep going.

140
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:43,880
Good basic skills.

141
00:07:45,440 --> 00:07:47,160
Come learn to cook with me later.

142
00:08:06,880 --> 00:08:08,560
Why are you being so sneaky?

143
00:08:08,840 --> 00:08:10,320
I have a surprise. Come.

144
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:15,960
Come on.

145
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:20,400
I'm not lying to you.

146
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:22,760
I'm tired of your games.

147
00:08:23,280 --> 00:08:24,480
Think about it carefully.

148
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:26,640
The troupe's future is at stake.

149
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:28,440
Suit yourself if you won't come.

150
00:08:49,360 --> 00:08:50,760
Surprised?

151
00:08:53,920 --> 00:08:55,360
Are you surprised?

152
00:08:57,440 --> 00:08:58,960
You're the boss this time.

153
00:08:59,760 --> 00:09:00,600
You bet I am.

154
00:09:01,760 --> 00:09:02,920
This way, please.

155
00:09:30,280 --> 00:09:32,360
This is all we have left.

156
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:34,040
Quite a surprise?

157
00:09:36,520 --> 00:09:37,400
It's all still here.

158
00:09:40,640 --> 00:09:41,880
Thank you, Master Gou.

159
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:46,080
Thank you, Master Zhou.

160
00:09:49,080 --> 00:09:50,200
Thank you, Master Qiu.

161
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:51,720
Hold on, hold on.

162
00:09:52,080 --> 00:09:53,360
There's one more surprise.

163
00:09:53,880 --> 00:09:54,720
Come on.

164
00:09:55,520 --> 00:09:56,400
Please.

165
00:10:02,640 --> 00:10:03,560
Master Gu?

166
00:10:05,280 --> 00:10:06,560
You're back.

167
00:10:13,160 --> 00:10:14,840
How did you get so old?

168
00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:16,640
That's just time for you.

169
00:10:19,040 --> 00:10:20,280
Surprised?

170
00:10:30,320 --> 00:10:33,880
The troupe did two modern plays, but nobody

171
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:35,160
really liked them.

172
00:10:36,480 --> 00:10:39,280
No one in the troupe can
perform the old opera.

173
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:42,600
People all say the troupe is failing.

174
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:45,200
Now, everyone in the troupe

175
00:10:45,200 --> 00:10:47,520
is discouraged and listless,

176
00:10:47,520 --> 00:10:48,720
barely hanging on.

177
00:10:48,720 --> 00:10:49,600
Whose fault is that?

178
00:10:50,120 --> 00:10:50,960
Your own.

179
00:10:51,440 --> 00:10:54,120
We warned you to prepare early on.

180
00:10:54,800 --> 00:10:56,360
How did you snap at us?

181
00:10:56,800 --> 00:10:58,080
I'm just a donkey.

182
00:10:58,800 --> 00:11:00,160
Wherever the whip strikes,

183
00:11:00,560 --> 00:11:01,760
I just pull along.

184
00:11:01,760 --> 00:11:03,600
Have you ever heard a donkey tell a whip

185
00:11:03,600 --> 00:11:04,520
where to strike?

186
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:06,760
What's the situation of the troupe?

187
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:10,720
The county leaders are very unhappy.

188
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:13,600
So, Huang Zhengjing wants the old opera.

189
00:11:14,200 --> 00:11:15,840
Which one exactly?

190
00:11:16,400 --> 00:11:17,600
Bi Shang Liang Shan.

191
00:11:18,760 --> 00:11:21,480
The Qinqiang opera has so many classics.

192
00:11:22,040 --> 00:11:25,040
Why start with a difficult adapted play?

193
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:28,920
Huang Zhengjing thinks it's safe.

194
00:11:29,960 --> 00:11:31,000
Aren't others as safe?

195
00:11:33,320 --> 00:11:34,160
Back then,

196
00:11:34,720 --> 00:11:36,720
when the troupe did Hong Hu Chi Wei Dui,

197
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:39,080
Huang Zhengjing wanted to be the best.

198
00:11:39,320 --> 00:11:40,520
Fighting for first in the district.

199
00:11:40,840 --> 00:11:41,680
And the result?

200
00:11:41,960 --> 00:11:43,400
Hu Sanyuan's single blast

201
00:11:43,840 --> 00:11:45,000
took Nail's life.

202
00:11:45,440 --> 00:11:47,280
And almost took his own.

203
00:11:47,640 --> 00:11:49,440
That changed Huang Zhengjing's fate, too.

204
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:52,320
Otherwise, Huang Zhengjing would have left.

205
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:54,440
If he had left,

206
00:11:54,440 --> 00:11:56,200
would the troupe be in this bad situation?

207
00:11:57,600 --> 00:11:59,400
That's because your leader is useless.

208
00:11:59,400 --> 00:12:01,400
Why blame Hu Sanyuan?

209
00:12:01,760 --> 00:12:03,520
What could Huang Zhengjing do?

210
00:12:03,840 --> 00:12:05,720
Did he want to control everything?

211
00:12:06,400 --> 00:12:07,600
Now he's a hands-off boss.

212
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:08,720
No one knows what he does.

213
00:12:09,160 --> 00:12:11,000
He stays in his office all day long,

214
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:12,000
doing who knows what.

215
00:12:12,640 --> 00:12:13,800
Now that you're back,

216
00:12:14,160 --> 00:12:15,920
I feel much more at ease.

217
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:17,240
But I don't.

218
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:18,480
Why?

219
00:12:18,480 --> 00:12:20,400
The excerpt Ye Ben from Bi Shang Liang Shan

220
00:12:20,880 --> 00:12:22,960
is extremely challenging for male actors.

221
00:12:23,840 --> 00:12:25,960
Lin Chong's singing,
acting, and recitation

222
00:12:26,480 --> 00:12:27,920
are all extremely complex.

223
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:29,800
That's why

224
00:12:30,880 --> 00:12:33,360
we're inviting you four
veteran artists back.

225
00:12:33,800 --> 00:12:35,640
Teach the kids in the troupe.

226
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:37,920
Let me tell you.

227
00:12:38,760 --> 00:12:39,720
I came back this time

228
00:12:40,240 --> 00:12:41,840
hoping, while I still can,

229
00:12:42,640 --> 00:12:44,360
to join my old partners and perform

230
00:12:45,160 --> 00:12:46,440
a few opera excerpts.

231
00:12:47,640 --> 00:12:48,920
What do you want to perform?

232
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:50,120
Zhou Ren Hui Fu.

233
00:12:50,360 --> 00:12:51,640
Put that aside for now.

234
00:12:53,160 --> 00:12:54,160
You Xi Hu.

235
00:12:54,600 --> 00:12:56,200
You two, set those aside first.

236
00:12:57,080 --> 00:12:57,920
Why?

237
00:13:01,480 --> 00:13:03,320
The most urgent thing is that

238
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:06,600
the traditional opera needs successors.

239
00:13:07,160 --> 00:13:08,280
Let the kids do something

240
00:13:08,920 --> 00:13:09,880
for the troupe,

241
00:13:09,880 --> 00:13:11,200
give it blood and keep it alive.

242
00:13:12,320 --> 00:13:13,840
Or the troupe is beyond saving.

243
00:13:15,240 --> 00:13:16,080
Well,

244
00:13:16,320 --> 00:13:17,160
you head back first.

245
00:13:17,520 --> 00:13:18,480
We'll talk it over.

246
00:13:49,560 --> 00:13:50,800
About us performing opera,

247
00:13:51,400 --> 00:13:52,560
maybe

248
00:13:52,560 --> 00:13:53,600
we put it on hold.

249
00:13:53,600 --> 00:13:54,680
On hold?

250
00:13:55,040 --> 00:13:57,040
We're already neck-deep in dirt.

251
00:13:57,040 --> 00:13:59,720
Wait longer, you'll sing in the underworld.

252
00:14:00,320 --> 00:14:02,480
But what else can we do, given the troupe?

253
00:14:03,280 --> 00:14:04,600
We have to save it first.

254
00:14:04,600 --> 00:14:05,560
But how?

255
00:14:05,880 --> 00:14:08,200
Call a doctor when it's in the coffin?

256
00:14:08,960 --> 00:14:10,040
You think you can pull off

257
00:14:10,040 --> 00:14:11,160
a miraculous cure?

258
00:14:11,160 --> 00:14:12,360
I can't do it alone,

259
00:14:12,360 --> 00:14:14,040
but the four of us can.

260
00:14:14,040 --> 00:14:14,920
Let's give it

261
00:14:14,920 --> 00:14:16,160
a shot together.

262
00:14:16,160 --> 00:14:17,280
There might still be hope.

263
00:14:17,280 --> 00:14:18,760
So what if there is?

264
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:21,600
Paving the way for Huang Zhengjing?

265
00:14:22,240 --> 00:14:23,360
If you want to be his stepping stone,

266
00:14:23,360 --> 00:14:25,200
go ahead, but leave me out of it.

267
00:14:25,800 --> 00:14:27,880
He's walked all over me for 20 years,

268
00:14:27,880 --> 00:14:29,040
and I've had enough.

269
00:14:29,040 --> 00:14:31,280
Who said anything about helping him?

270
00:14:32,240 --> 00:14:34,320
You two need to talk this out.

271
00:14:34,320 --> 00:14:35,880
No need

272
00:14:35,880 --> 00:14:37,760
to get all worked up.

273
00:14:38,120 --> 00:14:40,160
You had tempers when you were young,

274
00:14:40,560 --> 00:14:41,800
I get that.

275
00:14:41,800 --> 00:14:42,920
But look how old we are now.

276
00:14:42,920 --> 00:14:44,280
That fire should be long gone.

277
00:14:44,600 --> 00:14:45,800
Why still so angry?

278
00:14:45,800 --> 00:14:46,720
Just hot air.

279
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:48,940
- Let's go have tea.
- Sure.

280
00:14:48,960 --> 00:14:50,520
You two, keep arguing.

281
00:14:50,840 --> 00:14:52,840
Call us when you settle it.

282
00:14:53,080 --> 00:14:54,280
Silly, get moving.

283
00:14:54,620 --> 00:14:55,920
- Waiting to get scolded?
- Come on.

284
00:14:56,120 --> 00:14:57,030
Let's go.

285
00:15:04,840 --> 00:15:06,760
Argue, then. You're tough.

286
00:15:06,760 --> 00:15:08,120
You go first.

287
00:15:13,040 --> 00:15:14,520
Look at you.

288
00:15:17,840 --> 00:15:19,160
I drank too much last time.

289
00:15:19,760 --> 00:15:22,360
That talk about your apprentice

290
00:15:22,920 --> 00:15:23,800
was just drunk talk.

291
00:15:26,920 --> 00:15:27,760
Sir.

292
00:15:27,880 --> 00:15:29,720
I was wrong, okay?

293
00:15:31,640 --> 00:15:33,000
How could you ever be wrong?

294
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:35,200
You're always right.

295
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:36,800
Still sulking?

296
00:15:39,520 --> 00:15:40,360
I'm serious.

297
00:15:41,720 --> 00:15:44,240
In times like these, you still

298
00:15:44,760 --> 00:15:46,360
trained such a fine apprentice.

299
00:15:47,560 --> 00:15:49,000
That couldn't have been easy.

300
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:50,200
So you do know.

301
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:51,600
Of course, I know.

302
00:15:52,640 --> 00:15:53,960
I also know

303
00:15:53,960 --> 00:15:55,360
why you all risked it

304
00:15:55,600 --> 00:15:57,120
to save these opera costumes

305
00:15:57,120 --> 00:15:58,360
from the furnace.

306
00:16:00,640 --> 00:16:02,680
Wasn't it so that one day someone

307
00:16:02,680 --> 00:16:03,960
could wear them again?

308
00:16:05,040 --> 00:16:06,200
If no one ever wears them,

309
00:16:06,880 --> 00:16:08,960
won't they just turn to ash in the end?

310
00:16:09,960 --> 00:16:10,800
Right?

311
00:16:14,240 --> 00:16:15,720
I'm not trying to argue with you.

312
00:16:17,360 --> 00:16:18,720
The troupe is in such a mess.

313
00:16:19,840 --> 00:16:21,760
I'm worried you'll be left
holding the mess,

314
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:24,760
with no show, just dirt all over you.

315
00:16:28,640 --> 00:16:29,560
Sorry.

316
00:16:29,920 --> 00:16:31,400
I'm late. What did you need me for?

317
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:34,400
The four of us have decided.

318
00:16:35,520 --> 00:16:36,640
We'll do as you said.

319
00:16:37,320 --> 00:16:38,320
That's great!

320
00:16:38,640 --> 00:16:40,280
I'll go start the preparations now.

321
00:16:44,840 --> 00:16:45,760
But we have conditions.

322
00:16:47,040 --> 00:16:47,880
What conditions?

323
00:16:48,680 --> 00:16:49,520
First,

324
00:16:50,120 --> 00:16:52,120
Huang Zhengjing must ask us in person.

325
00:16:54,080 --> 00:16:55,160
He has to come himself?

326
00:16:55,480 --> 00:16:57,160
So my word isn't good enough?

327
00:16:57,720 --> 00:16:58,560
That's different.

328
00:16:59,160 --> 00:17:00,880
You're just the one pulling the cart.

329
00:17:01,280 --> 00:17:03,720
The donkey doesn't get to
choose the driver.

330
00:17:07,720 --> 00:17:09,000
Fine, I'm the donkey.

331
00:17:09,480 --> 00:17:11,360
But even a donkey has its pride.

332
00:17:12,600 --> 00:17:14,080
Let's not worry about

333
00:17:14,080 --> 00:17:15,400
saving face right now.

334
00:17:15,880 --> 00:17:18,200
The troupe isn't an
old opera troupe anymore.

335
00:17:18,880 --> 00:17:21,200
Without pride, there is no substance.

336
00:17:23,560 --> 00:17:24,400
Fine.

337
00:17:24,680 --> 00:17:26,000
I'll go get Huang Zhengjing now.

338
00:17:30,320 --> 00:17:31,600
What is it now?

339
00:17:33,120 --> 00:17:34,360
Since it's the old opera,

340
00:17:34,840 --> 00:17:36,960
we decide how to rehearse it.

341
00:17:37,640 --> 00:17:40,160
Everything follows the old rules.

342
00:17:41,080 --> 00:17:41,960
Rest assured.

343
00:17:42,480 --> 00:17:44,640
Huang Zhengjing is just a layman.

344
00:17:44,920 --> 00:17:46,080
Besides, with your old opera,

345
00:17:46,080 --> 00:17:47,200
he won't get a say at all.

346
00:17:47,640 --> 00:17:50,080
What I fear most are so-called experts.

347
00:17:56,520 --> 00:17:57,480
You mean me?

348
00:17:57,960 --> 00:17:59,080
Once rehearsals begin,

349
00:17:59,600 --> 00:18:00,920
there can only be one voice.

350
00:18:01,600 --> 00:18:03,160
No scattered comments

351
00:18:03,160 --> 00:18:04,200
from all sides.

352
00:18:04,600 --> 00:18:06,600
It'll be chaos. We can't rehearse.

353
00:18:07,200 --> 00:18:08,640
You sit there and watch.

354
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:09,840
Okay.

355
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:16,040
Seriously?

356
00:18:16,040 --> 00:18:17,960
Can you just say it all at once?

357
00:18:17,960 --> 00:18:19,080
Once this show is over,

358
00:18:19,480 --> 00:18:20,320
it'll be

359
00:18:20,880 --> 00:18:22,280
our turn to perform, right?

360
00:18:26,080 --> 00:18:29,720
The troupe can't go on like this.

361
00:18:30,920 --> 00:18:33,120
If I get to call the shots later,

362
00:18:33,680 --> 00:18:34,960
those are tiny things.

363
00:18:35,240 --> 00:18:36,120
What do you mean?

364
00:18:37,040 --> 00:18:38,960
What do I mean? Think it over.

365
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:55,080
Why'd you stop that noise?

366
00:18:55,760 --> 00:18:57,800
What? I have to go myself?

367
00:19:00,280 --> 00:19:02,240
My rank isn't high enough.

368
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:04,480
Yours isn't high enough?

369
00:19:04,880 --> 00:19:05,880
Then what rank are they?

370
00:19:06,600 --> 00:19:08,160
All they want is respect.

371
00:19:09,040 --> 00:19:10,360
We show them some respect,

372
00:19:10,760 --> 00:19:12,520
and they'll return it tenfold.

373
00:19:13,120 --> 00:19:16,120
Besides, you're head of the troupe.

374
00:19:16,120 --> 00:19:17,800
So you should show up in person.

375
00:19:19,960 --> 00:19:21,280
The way I see it,

376
00:19:21,280 --> 00:19:23,800
the old opera troupe's bad habits are back.

377
00:19:24,200 --> 00:19:25,560
Give them an inch,

378
00:19:25,560 --> 00:19:26,920
and they'll ask for a mile.

379
00:19:26,920 --> 00:19:28,640
Give them a little, and they push it.

380
00:19:28,640 --> 00:19:30,040
Then they'll get cocky again.

381
00:19:30,920 --> 00:19:31,760
They won't.

382
00:19:32,560 --> 00:19:34,240
After all they've been through,

383
00:19:34,240 --> 00:19:35,600
even the proudest tail

384
00:19:35,880 --> 00:19:37,200
has been snapped by now.

385
00:19:37,720 --> 00:19:39,400
Those veteran artists, in the end,

386
00:19:39,400 --> 00:19:41,640
just want some dignity and respect.

387
00:19:42,400 --> 00:19:43,280
Let them have it.

388
00:19:48,840 --> 00:19:49,680
Troupe Leader.

389
00:19:57,560 --> 00:19:59,680
Troupe Leader is truly wise.

390
00:20:45,920 --> 00:20:46,840
Here they come.

391
00:20:56,200 --> 00:20:57,640
We're not staging Bi Shang Liang Shan.

392
00:20:59,360 --> 00:21:00,200
Why not?

393
00:21:00,960 --> 00:21:01,800
I tried.

394
00:21:04,120 --> 00:21:05,160
Where's Huang Zhengjing?

395
00:21:05,760 --> 00:21:07,680
Calling me a donkey flatters me.

396
00:21:08,080 --> 00:21:10,040
I'm just a mouse trapped
in a bellows. Getting grief

397
00:21:10,280 --> 00:21:11,280
from both sides.

398
00:21:12,040 --> 00:21:13,320
What's the point for me?

399
00:21:16,040 --> 00:21:17,800
You two are cut from the same cloth.

400
00:21:18,640 --> 00:21:20,800
The troupe isn't Huang Zhengjing's.

401
00:21:21,320 --> 00:21:23,600
Why wait for him to invite us back?

402
00:21:26,640 --> 00:21:27,760
So ungrateful.

403
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:31,640
My first condition is

404
00:21:31,640 --> 00:21:32,480
now void.

405
00:21:34,960 --> 00:21:36,520
Pushing his luck.

406
00:21:38,400 --> 00:21:40,040
Really thinks he's a big shot.

407
00:21:42,400 --> 00:21:43,600
Useless.

408
00:21:51,720 --> 00:21:52,720
What kind of move is this?

409
00:22:08,880 --> 00:22:10,480
Did you do what I asked?

410
00:22:11,040 --> 00:22:12,080
Do what?

411
00:22:13,200 --> 00:22:14,760
I told you to be more lively.

412
00:22:16,560 --> 00:22:17,480
Show me.

413
00:22:42,360 --> 00:22:43,520
What are you doing?

414
00:22:44,520 --> 00:22:46,360
Dancing. Disco.

415
00:22:46,360 --> 00:22:48,320
Have you lost it?

416
00:22:49,080 --> 00:22:51,400
I never saw your gift for the Chou role.

417
00:22:53,080 --> 00:22:53,920
Get down here.

418
00:22:54,920 --> 00:22:56,520
What's that attitude?

419
00:22:59,760 --> 00:23:01,320
Did you buy some new clothes?

420
00:23:03,320 --> 00:23:04,160
Why not?

421
00:23:06,280 --> 00:23:07,200
I'm clueless.

422
00:23:07,480 --> 00:23:08,960
Can't you learn from others?

423
00:23:09,400 --> 00:23:10,840
Look at what Chu Jiahe wears.

424
00:23:10,840 --> 00:23:11,720
Aren't they pretty?

425
00:23:12,080 --> 00:23:12,960
They are.

426
00:23:12,960 --> 00:23:14,360
So you do know what beauty is.

427
00:23:14,880 --> 00:23:16,920
What do audiences expect from a Dan role?

428
00:23:17,480 --> 00:23:19,240
They expect your beauty.

429
00:23:19,240 --> 00:23:20,880
Beauty in singing.

430
00:23:20,880 --> 00:23:22,200
Beauty in acting.

431
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:23,720
Beauty in the appearance.

432
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:26,560
Miss one, and you can't play the Dan role.

433
00:23:27,720 --> 00:23:31,080
Your strength is you can take hardship.

434
00:23:32,040 --> 00:23:34,040
Your flaw is that's all you know.

435
00:23:34,840 --> 00:23:35,840
Doesn't that make you

436
00:23:35,840 --> 00:23:37,240
a blockhead?

437
00:23:39,360 --> 00:23:40,400
Get what I'm saying?

438
00:23:42,320 --> 00:23:43,640
You really are a blockhead.

439
00:23:43,640 --> 00:23:44,520
I get it.

440
00:23:45,960 --> 00:23:47,880
Then hurry up and look your best!

441
00:24:25,840 --> 00:24:27,560
Kids in the back, settle down.

442
00:24:28,280 --> 00:24:29,240
We haven't held a

443
00:24:29,240 --> 00:24:30,960
creative meeting in a long time.

444
00:24:31,240 --> 00:24:32,640
Troupe Leader Huang

445
00:24:32,960 --> 00:24:34,320
has some family matters

446
00:24:34,320 --> 00:24:35,160
and can't make it.

447
00:24:35,480 --> 00:24:37,560
So I'll be filling in for him

448
00:24:37,560 --> 00:24:39,640
to host this creative meeting.

449
00:24:40,480 --> 00:24:41,320
First,

450
00:24:41,840 --> 00:24:43,800
I need to announce

451
00:24:43,800 --> 00:24:45,560
a major decision.

452
00:24:46,160 --> 00:24:47,160
The troupe

453
00:24:47,960 --> 00:24:49,960
will very soon

454
00:24:50,400 --> 00:24:53,200
stage the traditional opera

455
00:24:53,880 --> 00:24:55,320
Bi Shang Liang Shan.

456
00:24:57,480 --> 00:24:59,960
Even new plays fail.
Why stage the old opera?

457
00:25:01,520 --> 00:25:02,480
That's because

458
00:25:02,480 --> 00:25:04,040
your drumming is bad.

459
00:25:05,120 --> 00:25:06,000
Fine, fine.

460
00:25:07,280 --> 00:25:08,200
Next,

461
00:25:08,800 --> 00:25:11,800
I'll introduce our four veteran artists.

462
00:25:12,120 --> 00:25:13,320
Gou Cunzhong.

463
00:25:14,480 --> 00:25:15,760
Zhou Cunren.

464
00:25:16,320 --> 00:25:17,640
Qiu Cunyi.

465
00:25:17,640 --> 00:25:18,960
These three masters

466
00:25:18,960 --> 00:25:20,400
are familiar to you,

467
00:25:20,400 --> 00:25:21,400
so I won't introduce them.

468
00:25:25,280 --> 00:25:26,120
Go back.

469
00:25:29,720 --> 00:25:30,560
Next,

470
00:25:30,960 --> 00:25:32,480
I'd like to formally introduce

471
00:25:33,280 --> 00:25:34,880
Master Gu Cunxiao.

472
00:25:44,040 --> 00:25:45,640
- Nice.
- Impressive.

473
00:25:46,200 --> 00:25:47,480
Cool.

474
00:25:47,480 --> 00:25:48,440
Master Gu Cunxiao

475
00:25:48,440 --> 00:25:51,160
- was the star performer.
- Hu Hansan is back.

476
00:25:51,720 --> 00:25:54,520
You kids might not know him.

477
00:25:54,520 --> 00:25:56,280
Due to special circumstances,

478
00:25:56,880 --> 00:25:59,840
Master Gu Cunxiao left
the troupe years ago.

479
00:26:01,080 --> 00:26:03,160
But today, he's back.

480
00:26:03,880 --> 00:26:05,800
Together with the other three,

481
00:26:05,800 --> 00:26:07,200
he will jointly

482
00:26:07,200 --> 00:26:09,560
serve as Director of Bi Shang Liang Shan.

483
00:26:10,080 --> 00:26:11,640
Now, with warm applause,

484
00:26:11,640 --> 00:26:14,240
let's welcome our four directors.

485
00:26:15,980 --> 00:26:16,880
Directors?

486
00:26:16,880 --> 00:26:18,480
Why shake the coat to speak?

487
00:26:18,720 --> 00:26:19,560
No idea.

488
00:26:21,880 --> 00:26:23,080
Again. There it is.

489
00:26:23,080 --> 00:26:25,060
There it goes. Shaking the coat.

490
00:26:25,080 --> 00:26:25,920
No idea.

491
00:26:27,480 --> 00:26:28,760
Janitor. Grocery buyer. Gatekeeper.

492
00:26:28,760 --> 00:26:29,680
How did they become directors?

493
00:26:29,680 --> 00:26:31,920
Right? The gatekeeper, a director?

494
00:26:31,960 --> 00:26:32,800
Feng Xiaoxiao!

495
00:26:33,760 --> 00:26:34,720
What are you muttering?

496
00:26:35,240 --> 00:26:36,080
Stand up!

497
00:26:36,480 --> 00:26:37,320
Say it loud.

498
00:26:38,280 --> 00:26:41,120
Master Gu's shaking the coat is impressive.

499
00:26:41,520 --> 00:26:43,090
Keep your admiration to yourself.

500
00:26:43,090 --> 00:26:44,010
Sit down.

501
00:26:44,010 --> 00:26:44,890
Okay.

502
00:26:45,600 --> 00:26:46,880
The traditional opera

503
00:26:47,880 --> 00:26:50,680
and the modern play share the same goals

504
00:26:51,040 --> 00:26:52,680
through different means.

505
00:26:53,640 --> 00:26:55,680
The traditional opera emphasizes

506
00:26:55,920 --> 00:26:56,960
singing,

507
00:26:56,960 --> 00:26:58,200
reciting,

508
00:26:58,200 --> 00:26:59,040
acting...

509
00:26:59,480 --> 00:27:00,720
What are you humming for?

510
00:27:04,320 --> 00:27:07,720
It's about singing, reciting,
acting, and combat.

511
00:27:07,720 --> 00:27:08,880
I believe that

512
00:27:09,280 --> 00:27:11,560
under the guidance of our four directors,

513
00:27:12,120 --> 00:27:15,280
they will show their signature skills

514
00:27:15,680 --> 00:27:18,640
and lead all the actors of the troupe

515
00:27:18,640 --> 00:27:20,400
to make the show a success!

516
00:27:20,400 --> 00:27:21,240
Great!

517
00:27:22,360 --> 00:27:23,200
Great!

518
00:27:25,600 --> 00:27:27,160
Slice the potatoes thinner.

519
00:27:27,160 --> 00:27:28,800
They look like shoe insoles.

520
00:27:28,800 --> 00:27:29,720
This is a radish.

521
00:27:29,720 --> 00:27:30,680
A radish?

522
00:27:30,680 --> 00:27:32,360
You don't cut them the same way?

523
00:27:33,400 --> 00:27:34,680
You always have an excuse.

524
00:27:36,400 --> 00:27:38,400
Wash these vegetables thoroughly.

525
00:27:38,920 --> 00:27:39,920
What are you looking at?

526
00:27:47,120 --> 00:27:48,760
- It's a circus.
- Look at the Dan role.

527
00:27:49,560 --> 00:27:50,480
Get back to work.

528
00:27:50,480 --> 00:27:51,600
During the circular walk...

529
00:27:51,600 --> 00:27:52,440
Whose kid?

530
00:27:53,120 --> 00:27:53,960
Leave

531
00:27:54,040 --> 00:27:55,000
if you aren't supposed to be here.

532
00:27:57,320 --> 00:27:59,000
When she's doing the circular walk,

533
00:27:59,000 --> 00:28:01,280
she must tuck in the stomach, lift the hips,

534
00:28:01,280 --> 00:28:02,840
relax the shoulders, straighten the back,

535
00:28:02,840 --> 00:28:04,520
stretch the neck, lift the head,

536
00:28:05,080 --> 00:28:06,760
and sink breath.

537
00:28:07,200 --> 00:28:08,960
Point your toes forward.

538
00:28:12,400 --> 00:28:13,760
No showing from under your skirt.

539
00:28:13,760 --> 00:28:16,280
Keep your torso still and glide along.

540
00:28:16,600 --> 00:28:19,600
That's how you make
the circle walk elegant.

541
00:28:19,600 --> 00:28:21,200
What do the audiences see?

542
00:28:21,200 --> 00:28:22,600
Your beauty.

543
00:28:23,040 --> 00:28:25,160
You must not wobble or sway.

544
00:28:25,160 --> 00:28:26,000
Who would watch that?

545
00:28:26,000 --> 00:28:26,840
Otherwise,

546
00:28:27,520 --> 00:28:30,200
you won't be the
chief military instructor's

547
00:28:30,200 --> 00:28:31,480
fair lady,

548
00:28:32,040 --> 00:28:34,360
and you'll just be a woman
from a Production Team.

549
00:28:37,000 --> 00:28:37,840
Don't laugh.

550
00:28:38,720 --> 00:28:41,280
You thief!

551
00:28:44,520 --> 00:28:45,440
Watch me again.

552
00:28:45,440 --> 00:28:46,520
What's there to look at?

553
00:28:46,720 --> 00:28:47,920
That old man's opera singing

554
00:28:47,920 --> 00:28:50,000
isn't worth watching. Go start the fire.

555
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:52,320
This is how you look charming and graceful.

556
00:28:52,320 --> 00:28:53,520
Keep your upper body still.

557
00:28:53,520 --> 00:28:54,920
Your feet are drifting.

558
00:28:55,200 --> 00:28:56,500
- Keep your torso still.
- Stop watching.

559
00:28:56,520 --> 00:28:57,600
Your feet are drifting.

560
00:28:57,600 --> 00:28:58,680
Love what you do.

561
00:29:19,000 --> 00:29:22,080
You thief!

562
00:29:34,880 --> 00:29:37,160
Slash. Thrust.

563
00:29:37,160 --> 00:29:38,120
Too high!

564
00:29:38,120 --> 00:29:40,000
Kid, over here. Right here.

565
00:29:40,560 --> 00:29:42,000
Remember that. Next.

566
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:43,240
One, two, three.

567
00:29:43,400 --> 00:29:45,520
Slash. Move.

568
00:29:50,320 --> 00:29:51,240
Where are you looking?

569
00:29:51,240 --> 00:29:53,080
Ready? Pull.

570
00:29:53,080 --> 00:29:53,920
One.

571
00:29:54,920 --> 00:29:56,480
- Two.
- Bow like you mean it.

572
00:29:56,480 --> 00:29:57,840
- This way.
- Three.

573
00:29:57,840 --> 00:29:58,680
Look this way.

574
00:29:58,960 --> 00:29:59,800
Go.

575
00:30:21,880 --> 00:30:22,720
He Dachui!

576
00:30:24,200 --> 00:30:25,040
He Dachui!

577
00:30:29,800 --> 00:30:30,920
He Dachui!

578
00:30:32,980 --> 00:30:33,880
Troupe Leader.

579
00:30:33,880 --> 00:30:34,920
What are you doing here?

580
00:30:35,320 --> 00:30:36,160
Rehearsing.

581
00:30:36,400 --> 00:30:37,800
Go to the rehearsal room then!

582
00:30:38,320 --> 00:30:39,840
The rehearsal room and the canteen

583
00:30:39,840 --> 00:30:41,560
are all full of actors.

584
00:30:41,560 --> 00:30:42,760
You still can't play the drums here.

585
00:30:43,040 --> 00:30:44,280
We were in the courtyard,

586
00:30:44,280 --> 00:30:45,760
but we scared the baby.

587
00:30:45,760 --> 00:30:46,800
So, we ended up here.

588
00:30:46,800 --> 00:30:48,280
Not here either. Go!

589
00:30:51,440 --> 00:30:53,440
ظآزHusband and wifeظآز

590
00:30:54,240 --> 00:30:56,920
ظآزTears and bloodظآز

591
00:30:56,920 --> 00:31:00,360
ظآزHard to part waysظآز

592
00:31:08,040 --> 00:31:09,000
Go!

593
00:31:09,760 --> 00:31:10,720
My lady!

594
00:31:11,120 --> 00:31:12,640
- My lord!
- Hurry up!

595
00:31:12,820 --> 00:31:13,680
My lady!

596
00:31:13,680 --> 00:31:15,720
Stop, stop, stop.

597
00:31:17,680 --> 00:31:19,280
How many times must I tell you?

598
00:31:19,800 --> 00:31:21,200
You keep slouching your back.

599
00:31:21,200 --> 00:31:22,880
You're playing Lady Lin.

600
00:31:23,320 --> 00:31:25,000
Don't sway like a snake,

601
00:31:25,360 --> 00:31:27,840
drifting in the wind without poise.

602
00:31:27,840 --> 00:31:30,120
Stay steady. You are Lady Lin.

603
00:31:30,680 --> 00:31:31,760
You want this role?

604
00:31:32,960 --> 00:31:33,800
Go ahead.

605
00:31:34,600 --> 00:31:36,520
I've said it before. As a Dan role,

606
00:31:36,520 --> 00:31:39,120
relax the shoulders
and straighten the back

607
00:31:39,120 --> 00:31:40,480
for proper posture.

608
00:31:40,740 --> 00:31:41,640
Also,

609
00:31:41,640 --> 00:31:43,480
lift the wrist and flip the sleeve.

610
00:31:43,480 --> 00:31:45,320
Lift the wrist and flip the sleeve. Got it?

611
00:31:45,720 --> 00:31:47,280
That's how you show your charm.

612
00:31:47,280 --> 00:31:48,800
Lift the wrist and flip the sleeve.

613
00:31:50,280 --> 00:31:51,120
Now try.

614
00:31:52,240 --> 00:31:53,880
I can't. Something's in my eye.

615
00:31:56,560 --> 00:31:58,240
Director Gu, what should we do?

616
00:32:07,360 --> 00:32:08,200
Mi Lan.

617
00:32:09,120 --> 00:32:09,960
Listen to him.

618
00:32:10,760 --> 00:32:11,600
Qing'e.

619
00:32:12,400 --> 00:32:13,920
Stir constantly in the wok.

620
00:32:14,400 --> 00:32:15,680
Or it won't cook evenly.

621
00:32:15,920 --> 00:32:17,920
I used to stir-fry with a small ladle.

622
00:32:18,320 --> 00:32:21,380
The food would fly up and down, you know?

623
00:32:21,400 --> 00:32:22,440
Without spilling a single drop.

624
00:32:23,040 --> 00:32:25,160
This is manual labor.

625
00:32:25,770 --> 00:32:26,780
Song,

626
00:32:26,800 --> 00:32:27,820
come here.

627
00:32:28,400 --> 00:32:30,320
You take over this low-skill work.

628
00:32:30,680 --> 00:32:31,920
I'm the head chef, you know?

629
00:32:32,360 --> 00:32:33,760
What head chef does this all day?

630
00:32:38,960 --> 00:32:39,800
Qing'e.

631
00:32:40,200 --> 00:32:41,040
Come here.

632
00:32:41,120 --> 00:32:42,040
Come rub my shoulders.

633
00:32:42,360 --> 00:32:43,960
Thump my back. I'm so sore.

634
00:32:45,960 --> 00:32:48,520
Apprentices used to massage their master.

635
00:32:48,760 --> 00:32:50,200
It was perfectly normal.

636
00:32:50,600 --> 00:32:51,720
Traditional rules.

637
00:32:52,320 --> 00:32:53,160
Come here.

638
00:32:53,880 --> 00:32:54,720
Come here!

639
00:32:56,280 --> 00:32:58,120
Laidi, the fire is dying.

640
00:32:58,390 --> 00:32:59,500
- Got it.
- Hurry and add some coal.

641
00:32:59,880 --> 00:33:01,640
I was cooking just fine earlier.

642
00:33:01,640 --> 00:33:03,480
Why did it die when you took over?

643
00:33:04,240 --> 00:33:06,160
Just admit you lack the skill.

644
00:33:06,840 --> 00:33:09,840
Big talkers get struck by lightning.

645
00:33:10,960 --> 00:33:12,080
Speak normally to me.

646
00:33:12,080 --> 00:33:13,360
I don't understand your idioms.

647
00:33:17,200 --> 00:33:18,160
Gou.

648
00:33:19,160 --> 00:33:20,000
Gou!

649
00:33:20,920 --> 00:33:21,800
Alright, alright.

650
00:33:24,480 --> 00:33:25,520
Our Security Section

651
00:33:25,520 --> 00:33:27,200
is truly full of hidden talents.

652
00:33:27,200 --> 00:33:28,040
All these years,

653
00:33:28,120 --> 00:33:30,040
your talent has been buried.

654
00:33:32,800 --> 00:33:33,680
What is it?

655
00:33:34,080 --> 00:33:36,040
Your Section Chief said you work hard,

656
00:33:36,040 --> 00:33:37,400
so I came to check on you.

657
00:33:38,320 --> 00:33:39,560
Don't be so formal.

658
00:33:39,960 --> 00:33:42,000
Master Gou, we're all
in the Security Section.

659
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:43,800
We're family, aren't we?

660
00:33:43,800 --> 00:33:44,680
Exactly.

661
00:33:45,240 --> 00:33:47,280
Master Gou, can I ask you something?

662
00:33:48,480 --> 00:33:49,320
Go ahead.

663
00:33:51,080 --> 00:33:53,120
Can I play Lin Chong's wife?

664
00:33:55,880 --> 00:33:57,240
That's not up to me.

665
00:33:57,630 --> 00:33:58,520
Master Gou,

666
00:33:58,520 --> 00:34:00,680
I've been an extra my whole life.

667
00:34:00,680 --> 00:34:02,120
I've never played the lead,

668
00:34:02,560 --> 00:34:04,800
or even a decent role.

669
00:34:04,800 --> 00:34:05,760
If I don't do it now,

670
00:34:06,280 --> 00:34:07,880
I might never get the chance.

671
00:34:08,520 --> 00:34:10,560
I've learned everything you taught me.

672
00:34:10,560 --> 00:34:11,600
Just watch me.

673
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:18,600
You thief!

674
00:34:18,600 --> 00:34:19,440
How was that?

675
00:34:20,400 --> 00:34:21,240
Not bad?

676
00:34:22,760 --> 00:34:23,600
Gou.

677
00:34:23,880 --> 00:34:24,720
Master Gou?

678
00:34:29,560 --> 00:34:30,400
Okay?

679
00:34:31,480 --> 00:34:32,320
You think?

680
00:34:33,280 --> 00:34:34,320
Why not?

681
00:34:36,200 --> 00:34:38,080
If we need Lin Chong's mother next time,

682
00:34:38,080 --> 00:34:39,320
I'll definitely let her play the role.

683
00:34:48,960 --> 00:34:50,920
What is this? What are you even doing?

684
00:34:53,680 --> 00:34:54,520
Like this.

685
00:34:54,920 --> 00:34:55,760
Not like this.

686
00:34:57,920 --> 00:34:58,760
Go.

687
00:35:16,640 --> 00:35:17,480
Small.

688
00:35:18,280 --> 00:35:19,120
Walk.

689
00:35:19,640 --> 00:35:20,520
Big.

690
00:35:21,520 --> 00:35:22,560
Small.

691
00:35:23,160 --> 00:35:24,000
Walk.

692
00:35:24,760 --> 00:35:25,840
Big.

693
00:35:25,840 --> 00:35:26,680
Small.

694
00:35:27,280 --> 00:35:28,840
Walk properly.

695
00:35:28,940 --> 00:35:34,820
(Recreate a new soul)

696
00:35:44,080 --> 00:35:45,080
Won't work?

697
00:35:49,800 --> 00:35:51,720
Always talking about "dear wife"...

698
00:35:51,720 --> 00:35:53,120
Stop, stop.

699
00:35:53,120 --> 00:35:54,120
Stop chatting.

700
00:35:54,120 --> 00:35:54,960
Stop chatting.

701
00:35:56,760 --> 00:35:57,720
Shoulders rounded.

702
00:35:58,320 --> 00:35:59,960
Your eyes. The mood.

703
00:36:00,240 --> 00:36:01,720
Okay, get ready.

704
00:36:12,340 --> 00:36:13,180
(Pastries)

705
00:36:25,660 --> 00:36:29,700
(Musical Feature Film:
Reverberations of Life)

706
00:36:52,440 --> 00:36:53,280
Kiss you?

707
00:36:53,760 --> 00:36:54,960
- Shanshan.
- Kiss whoever you want.

708
00:36:54,960 --> 00:36:58,200
- I'll kiss you.
- You're taking a huge risk.

709
00:36:59,520 --> 00:37:01,960
Your dad and I went to Huang Village.

710
00:37:02,600 --> 00:37:03,800
With your uncle...

711
00:37:04,120 --> 00:37:05,000
We went to Tian'anmen together.

712
00:37:05,000 --> 00:37:05,840
Stop pushing me.

713
00:37:06,420 --> 00:37:09,860
(Ningzhou Cinema)

714
00:37:10,600 --> 00:37:12,160
Give me a chance.

715
00:37:13,400 --> 00:37:15,400
What's wrong? Is the movie no good?

716
00:37:15,920 --> 00:37:17,360
Er Laizi, she's glaring at you.

717
00:37:18,960 --> 00:37:21,600
Stare at me again and
I'll gouge your eyes out.

718
00:37:21,600 --> 00:37:22,760
Scared?

719
00:37:23,240 --> 00:37:24,640
I'm not a monster.

720
00:37:24,640 --> 00:37:25,960
Er Laizi, get her!

721
00:37:27,900 --> 00:37:29,780
(Today's film: Reverberations of Life
Ticket price: 1 jiao)

722
00:37:39,960 --> 00:37:42,480
It's all about singing now,

723
00:37:42,480 --> 00:37:43,320
right?

724
00:37:45,200 --> 00:37:47,240
This singing part has nothing to do

725
00:37:47,920 --> 00:37:49,200
with my drumming.

726
00:37:49,200 --> 00:37:56,110
ظآزThe north wind blows hardظآز

727
00:37:57,490 --> 00:38:00,020
ظآزSharp as a knifeظآز

728
00:38:00,290 --> 00:38:03,900
ظآزSharp as a knifeظآز

729
00:38:06,480 --> 00:38:07,360
Stop!

730
00:38:09,520 --> 00:38:10,960
What now? Was I wrong again?

731
00:38:11,200 --> 00:38:12,040
Not you.

732
00:38:12,280 --> 00:38:13,200
It's the orchestra.

733
00:38:15,400 --> 00:38:16,240
What's wrong?

734
00:38:16,920 --> 00:38:18,920
Your drumming is way too loose,

735
00:38:19,640 --> 00:38:20,960
putting everyone to sleep.

736
00:38:21,640 --> 00:38:22,960
Nonsense.

737
00:38:23,360 --> 00:38:24,960
I was playing

738
00:38:24,960 --> 00:38:26,120
with the feeling.

739
00:38:26,120 --> 00:38:27,480
It had to be slow.

740
00:38:29,240 --> 00:38:31,160
Slow doesn't mean loose.

741
00:38:32,080 --> 00:38:33,800
Keep it slow, but with tension.

742
00:38:34,400 --> 00:38:36,120
Keep the pace measured.

743
00:38:36,120 --> 00:38:37,520
Keep the spirit flowing through.

744
00:38:37,520 --> 00:38:38,640
What were you playing?

745
00:38:38,880 --> 00:38:40,400
It's slow, but there's no tension.

746
00:38:40,720 --> 00:38:42,960
Like baggy old granny pants. It doesn't

747
00:38:42,960 --> 00:38:43,920
grab anyone.

748
00:38:44,640 --> 00:38:46,400
What kind of nonsense is that?

749
00:38:47,880 --> 00:38:48,720
Fine.

750
00:38:48,880 --> 00:38:51,400
Come on. You play it.

751
00:38:51,400 --> 00:38:53,840
Play those baggy pants with feeling.

752
00:38:53,840 --> 00:38:55,120
I'm not the drummer.

753
00:38:55,320 --> 00:38:56,880
Then keep your mouth shut.

754
00:38:56,880 --> 00:38:58,040
Cut the nonsense.

755
00:38:58,640 --> 00:38:59,480
Who's talking nonsense?

756
00:38:59,840 --> 00:39:00,720
You.

757
00:39:00,720 --> 00:39:02,040
Keep playing like that,

758
00:39:02,040 --> 00:39:03,920
and you'll wreck the whole show!

759
00:39:03,920 --> 00:39:05,040
Nonsense!

760
00:39:05,520 --> 00:39:06,920
I've had enough of you!

761
00:39:06,920 --> 00:39:08,640
That lousy coat of yours!

762
00:39:08,640 --> 00:39:09,520
Flapping all over!

763
00:39:09,520 --> 00:39:10,920
A dumb dog acting like a guard dog!

764
00:39:10,920 --> 00:39:12,120
You're making me dizzy!

765
00:39:12,120 --> 00:39:13,640
The rehearsal's a mess, who's to blame?

766
00:39:13,640 --> 00:39:15,080
You blame this, blame that!

767
00:39:15,080 --> 00:39:17,200
I want to knock out every tooth you have!

768
00:39:17,640 --> 00:39:19,360
Do it! Knock them all out!

769
00:39:19,360 --> 00:39:20,640
Acting so tough?

770
00:39:21,280 --> 00:39:22,280
Screw you!

771
00:39:30,600 --> 00:39:32,060
Director Gu. Find the teeth.

772
00:39:32,080 --> 00:39:33,520
- No.
- His teeth fell out.

773
00:39:33,960 --> 00:39:35,560
Here, here, pick them up.

774
00:39:35,560 --> 00:39:36,400
The teeth are here.

775
00:39:36,880 --> 00:39:37,840
Pick them up.

776
00:39:43,000 --> 00:39:43,920
Come on, check.

777
00:39:44,160 --> 00:39:45,000
Is it okay now?

778
00:39:45,880 --> 00:39:46,720
It's fine.

779
00:39:47,560 --> 00:39:48,640
Try taking a bite.

780
00:39:49,640 --> 00:39:50,480
Seriously?

781
00:39:51,520 --> 00:39:53,200
I couldn't bite even with good teeth.

782
00:39:53,920 --> 00:39:55,080
My dear Pei,

783
00:39:55,400 --> 00:39:56,760
is anything else on you fake?

784
00:39:57,120 --> 00:39:59,120
It's all original, except the teeth.

785
00:40:00,200 --> 00:40:01,400
You were actually right.

786
00:40:02,160 --> 00:40:03,400
A real mess.

787
00:40:03,960 --> 00:40:04,800
Told you.

788
00:40:05,360 --> 00:40:06,600
Deal with it yourself.

789
00:40:09,160 --> 00:40:10,000
Master Gu.

790
00:40:11,280 --> 00:40:12,120
How are your teeth?

791
00:40:16,680 --> 00:40:18,680
He Dachui was sent to the hospital.

792
00:40:19,080 --> 00:40:21,040
His leg is swollen like a balloon.

793
00:40:21,480 --> 00:40:22,520
Save it!

794
00:40:22,520 --> 00:40:23,520
This isn't over!

795
00:40:23,760 --> 00:40:24,920
This isn't over!

796
00:40:25,920 --> 00:40:27,560
Master Zhou, please calm down.

797
00:40:27,560 --> 00:40:29,160
Come on, cool off. Sit down.

798
00:40:29,160 --> 00:40:30,840
Sit. Sit down.

799
00:40:31,040 --> 00:40:31,880
Sit.

800
00:40:33,040 --> 00:40:34,400
You didn't see him.

801
00:40:35,040 --> 00:40:37,480
That guy's a total mess now.

802
00:40:38,480 --> 00:40:40,160
Master Zhou, you went too hard.

803
00:40:40,160 --> 00:40:41,480
No idea what's with his bones.

804
00:40:41,880 --> 00:40:43,080
If they hadn't stopped me,

805
00:40:43,080 --> 00:40:44,760
I'd have put him on two crutches!

806
00:40:44,760 --> 00:40:46,480
Then who would play the drums?

807
00:40:47,800 --> 00:40:49,800
I'm not defending He Dachui.

808
00:40:50,160 --> 00:40:51,360
But if he doesn't drum,

809
00:40:51,760 --> 00:40:52,920
who in the troupe will?

810
00:40:54,240 --> 00:40:55,240
Wouldn't that be perfect?

811
00:40:55,920 --> 00:40:56,760
Just disband.

812
00:40:57,760 --> 00:40:58,920
Listen to yourself, Master Zhou.

813
00:40:58,920 --> 00:41:00,600
Does that sound like you?

814
00:41:01,640 --> 00:41:03,280
Look how far we've rehearsed.

815
00:41:04,280 --> 00:41:06,760
Cast and orchestra are in sync.

816
00:41:07,080 --> 00:41:08,320
We can't just call it quits.

817
00:41:13,720 --> 00:41:14,880
Let me tell you guys,

818
00:41:15,760 --> 00:41:18,400
rumors are flying in the troupe.

819
00:41:19,560 --> 00:41:21,320
People are saying the four of you

820
00:41:21,320 --> 00:41:22,520
are only good at putting on airs,

821
00:41:23,480 --> 00:41:24,880
and can't even direct a play.

822
00:41:24,880 --> 00:41:25,720
What?

823
00:41:26,560 --> 00:41:28,880
If we fall apart now,

824
00:41:29,240 --> 00:41:30,880
what will the troupe think of you?

825
00:41:40,920 --> 00:41:42,080
Is Master Gu okay?

826
00:41:42,520 --> 00:41:43,680
What could be wrong?

827
00:41:44,960 --> 00:41:47,040
He's old. His dentures are just loose.

828
00:41:49,320 --> 00:41:51,440
Go back. Don't worry about it.

829
00:41:52,280 --> 00:41:53,440
He sold steamed Mo his whole life.

830
00:41:53,440 --> 00:41:54,640
He's seen it all.

831
00:41:57,160 --> 00:41:58,920
Your uncle is so unreliable.

832
00:41:59,640 --> 00:42:01,320
He's never around when it matters.

833
00:42:01,720 --> 00:42:02,880
This is driving me crazy.

834
00:42:09,440 --> 00:42:10,760
Come on, shuffle the cards.

835
00:42:10,760 --> 00:42:11,640
Hurry it up.

836
00:42:13,320 --> 00:42:14,640
- Sir?
- You almost set the house on fire.

837
00:42:14,640 --> 00:42:15,460
You're here.

838
00:42:15,480 --> 00:42:16,440
Join us?

839
00:42:16,440 --> 00:42:17,680
Come on, join us.

840
00:42:17,680 --> 00:42:18,520
Not now.

841
00:42:19,000 --> 00:42:20,280
I need a word with Dachui.

842
00:42:20,280 --> 00:42:21,550
- Leave for now.
- Let's go.

843
00:42:21,550 --> 00:42:22,880
But we were about to...

844
00:42:23,000 --> 00:42:23,880
- Go.
- Let's go.

845
00:42:23,880 --> 00:42:24,720
Let's go.

846
00:42:25,960 --> 00:42:26,800
Hurry.

847
00:42:27,280 --> 00:42:28,160
Shut the door.

848
00:42:28,160 --> 00:42:29,000
Okay.

849
00:42:30,000 --> 00:42:30,840
Come back later.

850
00:42:31,160 --> 00:42:32,920
Later? How's your leg?

851
00:42:33,360 --> 00:42:34,200
Still don't know yet.

852
00:42:34,200 --> 00:42:36,640
The X-ray won't be ready for three days.

853
00:42:36,640 --> 00:42:37,480
Where exactly?

854
00:42:38,000 --> 00:42:40,040
This spot keeps spasming.

855
00:42:40,040 --> 00:42:41,200
Right here, yeah?

856
00:42:41,200 --> 00:42:42,080
It keeps aching.

857
00:42:42,080 --> 00:42:42,920
Let me see.

858
00:42:44,480 --> 00:42:45,360
Looks fine

859
00:42:45,480 --> 00:42:47,040
to me. You can walk.

860
00:42:47,320 --> 00:42:48,560
Why did you act like that?

861
00:42:50,360 --> 00:42:52,040
Those four old guys

862
00:42:53,280 --> 00:42:54,680
couldn't rehearse their show.

863
00:42:55,080 --> 00:42:57,000
They blamed my drumming for it.

864
00:42:57,320 --> 00:42:58,360
Wouldn't you be mad too?

865
00:42:58,360 --> 00:42:59,840
You knew they were old guys.

866
00:43:00,320 --> 00:43:01,800
Why get physical with an old man?

867
00:43:02,280 --> 00:43:04,200
What if you really hurt him?

868
00:43:05,020 --> 00:43:06,940
=The Lead=
(Preview)

869
00:43:11,000 --> 00:43:12,280
Stop it! So annoying!

870
00:43:12,920 --> 00:43:14,570
That kid was born for the stage,

871
00:43:14,650 --> 00:43:16,760
and her fundamentals are rock solid.

872
00:43:16,760 --> 00:43:18,840
Our trainees are nowhere near her level.

873
00:43:18,840 --> 00:43:21,340
Can we pause rehearsals for
Bi Shang Liang Shan

874
00:43:21,400 --> 00:43:23,080
and switch to Yang Pai Feng first?

875
00:43:23,080 --> 00:43:23,930
Do you realize

876
00:43:23,930 --> 00:43:24,900
what it would mean

877
00:43:24,900 --> 00:43:26,040
if this show failed?

878
00:43:26,040 --> 00:43:27,640
A county-level troupe's standards

879
00:43:27,710 --> 00:43:29,470
end up worse than a disciple

880
00:43:29,470 --> 00:43:31,330
casually trained by a few old guys?

881
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:41,620
ظآزWhen I woke up and turned backظآز

882
00:43:43,090 --> 00:43:47,930
ظآزI wasn't sure where to goظآز

883
00:43:49,370 --> 00:43:53,560
ظآزWe met and brushed pastظآز

884
00:43:55,120 --> 00:44:02,420
ظآزYour shadow drifted out of sightظآز

885
00:44:16,790 --> 00:44:20,540
ظآزThe stove fire blazed in my dreamظآز

886
00:44:22,140 --> 00:44:27,710
ظآزLit up the tracks of pearly tearsظآز

887
00:44:28,830 --> 00:44:32,890
ظآزIn my dream, water sleeves flewظآز

888
00:44:34,020 --> 00:44:39,610
ظآزHiding a lifetime of loveظآز

889
00:44:40,770 --> 00:44:44,970
ظآزThe Qinling Mountains
crossed the stageظآز

890
00:44:46,010 --> 00:44:51,640
ظآزSpring water brewed strong wineظآز

891
00:44:52,810 --> 00:44:57,500
ظآزSheep moved through the valleyظآز

892
00:44:58,180 --> 00:45:03,350
ظآزIt felt like a promise
from another lifeظآز

893
00:45:04,020 --> 00:45:09,050
ظآزWhen I woke up and turned backظآز

894
00:45:10,080 --> 00:45:15,510
ظآزI wasn't sure where to goظآز

895
00:45:15,890 --> 00:45:21,170
ظآزIf I chose again, I'd still roamظآز

896
00:45:22,120 --> 00:45:27,930
ظآزAll over this sunlit plateauظآز

897
00:45:27,930 --> 00:45:33,350
ظآزThe dream ends; the curtain fallsظآز

898
00:45:33,900 --> 00:45:39,410
ظآزMoonlight washes off this stage makeupظآز

899
00:45:39,960 --> 00:45:44,920
ظآزThe one in the mirror wears gray hairظآز

900
00:45:45,940 --> 00:45:51,220
ظآزAlready sang all my joy and sorrowظآز

901
00:45:52,020 --> 00:46:01,050
ظآزAlready shouted across Qinchuan Plainظآز

